<T>__{cut to:}
<A>__{prince humperdinck, a man of incredible power and bearing, standing in his royal robes on a castle balcony. three others standing behind him: an old couple with crowns, the aging king and queen, and a dark bearded man who seems the prince's match in strength: this is count rugen.}
<C>__{humperdinck}
<P>__{(raises his hands, starts to speak)}
<D>__{my people ... a month from now, our country will have its 500th anniversary. on that sundown, i shall marry a lady who was once a commoner like yourselves }
<P>__{(pause)}
<D>__{ but perhaps you will not find her common now. would you like to meet her?}
<A>__{and the answering yessss booms like summer thunder.}
